It’s no secret that rapper Cassper Nyovest has done very well for himself, that’s because he is not afraid to flaunt his achievements. The flashy cars he drives, expensive watches he wears and the place he calls home, say a lot about how he has come. While many might call it ‘bragging’ some will call it ‘inspiration’, either way life has probably never been better for Abuti Fill Up. The Tito Mboweni hit-maker took to social media recently to show off part of his huge house in a short video. "The place I call home. The yard is hectare, the crib is cool but the price mad! Okay I'm lying the crib is mad too but dawg I had to get the f**king castle," read part of his tweet.  